<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Suesc</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I hold the parts for one bracer.  I will shortly own two bars of platinum (is that right? 2 bars for one bracer? Seems odd...) I realize that costs vary among servers, but can I have an idea of the cost to get my bars of platinum enchanted?  <P>My next step will be to find an enchanter to do this. Unfortunately, those in my guild are not high enough level yet, so I will be "cold calling" my prospects.<P>As always, thanks for your help  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Leonidas<BR>Level 30.2 Cleric of Mith Marr<BR>Order of Kynigos<BR>Brell Serillis server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Seliris</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have only paid for maybe 2 out of the 12-15 bars i have gotten enchanted.<P>Mostly people on BBane know me, and a high lvl cleric friend is always appreciated.<P>*shrug*<P>The only cask I ever paid was 10-30pp per bar though, if memory serves correctly.<P>------------------<BR>-Seliris Caileadair<BR>High Cleric of Clachan Brigh<BR>Bristlebane Server<BR>*i dont get angry at the game, just the people playing it*<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mlar D'Kath</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I would estimate that it might cost 10-20pp per bar or so.I also had to use /auc offering to pay,but once the enchanters knew it was for a quest none of them charged  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">.<P>Just keep the bars on you and some pp and keep auctioning,but do not spam the zone.<P><BR>Mlar D'Kath<BR>Priest of Innoruuk</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gilt</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">When doing the quests for the armor, I guess I had pretty good luck with my platinum bars…<P>To somewhat repeat what Mlar said, make it known that it’s for a quest in your auction; people are usually more helpful then. (Let’s face it: very few enchanters actually need the money, and it’s just a few mana points.) In fact, I even asked an enchanter or two to buy the bars for me in the first place. Their charisma saved me about 20 plats. <P>By the way, I had no idea the Cleric quest armor was gold when I chose my first name. I started with a Necro friend who was called Cynn and it was meant to be a pun, though I did sort of  have the real meaning in the back of my head. I absolutely love it that it worked out this way. <P>Gilt Helamakir<BR>35th Level Cleric of Quellious<BR>Brell Serillis<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kenobe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I had a Bard guildmate buy my bars for me, saved me a few pp.  I then went to EC on Sat and did a shout/ooc/auc mentioning they were for a quest.  There are ususally a few high level enchanters selling their wares who will do it for free.  I didn't have to pay for any of the 3 I had enchanted so far. <BR>Think you will find in this setting mana is meaningless for them while they are seeling stuff and its always nice for anyone to have an IOU from a cleric  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>good luck!<P>------------------<BR>Kenobe Wan<BR>31 Human Cleric<BR>&lt;Praxium&gt;<BR>Cazic-Thule</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">shashi</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well I paid about 100pp in one sitting for my bars to be enchanted... but then again I found a really nice enchanter that was willing to sit down with me for a few minutes and enchant like 8 bars for me at once. He didn't even ask for a specific amount, just asked me to donate what it was worth to me and so I handed him what was left in my pp slot after buying all the bars. (Enchant Plat is not a cheap spell mana-wise btw.)<P>On the most part tho, as long as you tell the enchanter what your using them for they'll be more than happy to enchant for free or a small donation. Some have even bought the bars for me so I could get a better price.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Cinlai Shaestari<BR>Lanys T'Vyl</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Troas Merwind</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Occasionally enchanters will carry plat bars on them - you may get lucky in EC.  One thing that worked for me a couple of times:  have the enchanter buy the bar, but pay the enchanter a bit over what I would have paid the vendor.  If his faction and CHA are high,  it could easily be 10pp less for him to buy it than you - he gets cash for his time, and you only paid what you would have anyway...<P>------------------<BR>Troas Merwind<BR>Cleric of Tunare<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Suesc</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thanks so much, everyone )</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
